@NODE "Usage" "Usage"
@TOC "MAIN"
@{b}Usage:@{ub}

From CLI
    C:Apatch >NIL:

    It's not suggested to run this patch:
    À more than once(one function is branching back to previous address of a routine, which may cause slowdown in extremal cases)
    À in user-startup or later 

(if you are running FasterBlit6.6 by Arthur Hagen make sure that APatch is started just after it)

@{b}Because It's still BETA the patch won't remove itself if run twice and no memory will be freed.@{ub} 
@ENDNODE
@NODE "Install" "Installation"
@TOC "MAIN"
@{b}Installation:@{ub}

    Copy APatch to your C: directory
add C:APatch >NIL: to your startup-sequence just after SETPATCH or PatchControl
(if that doesn't work then move it before setpatch (probably on 040 & 060 ))
Simple, eh?

If you are using FasterBlit6.6 by Arthur Hagen then put it before APatch in your startup-sequence.
@ENDNODE
@NODE "Requirements" "Requirements"
@TOC "MAIN"
@{b}Requirements:@{ub}

    The things you need to run APatch:

    À Amiga [or maybe even UAE ;-) ] with 68020 or better

    À Kickstart 3.0 (It may work with 2.1, but don't expect me to write a special version for 1.3! Get real, upgrade!)

