@NODE "Bugs" "Bugs"
@TOC "MAIN"
@{b}Bugs:@{ub}

    À First, if you have no real FAST memory installed this patch will slow down your amiga not because it sucks, but because CPU has to share access cycles to chipram with other custom chips. That's why there is no point in running this or any other speedup patch on amiga that is equipped with chip-ram only! PCMCIA ram cards are too slow too...Do yourself a favor and get some real 32-bit FAST-RAM!

    À Second, I only have ec020 here...and not working A4000...Volunteer to fix my A4000, and I'll make sure that the routines are cache/burst/copyback/??? aware...:-)

    À Third, some anti-viruses will report changed vectors...Unfortunately, I can't put those patches to your ROM chip...All vectors @{"patched" LINK "APatch"} by APatch should be within ~6kb area (for now, in the future this area will be bigger). Moreover, VirusZ is able to recognize some patches (only the few first bytes are checked)

    À Fourth, it's still BETA!

    À Fifth, APatch should be started before anything that bangs autointerrupt vectors! (8n1.device ,etc...)
@{JCENTER}
Please send bug reports, suggestions and comments via E-Mail to: 
@{i}lucky@silly.com@{ui}@{UJCENTER}
@ENDNODE
